eval("__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);\n/* harmony export */ __webpack_require__.d(__webpack_exports__, {\n/* harmony export */   CONTENT: () => (/* binding */ CONTENT)\n/* harmony export */ });\n// ============================================================\n// CONTENT DATA — All LP, zodiac, western, careers, personalYear\n// ============================================================\nconst CONTENT = {\n    numerology: {\n        1: `# 1 Lifepath\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here as a leader - independent and ambitious, somebody who takes responsibility and doesn't take \"no\" for an answer. Quick tempered and argumentative, you say things how they are instead of sugarcoating it which often leads to conflict. You are good at giving advice but not that good at taking it, your arrogance leads you to learn things the hard way. Your drive and willpower is the leading force behind your actions - you get things done, even if it means doing it alone.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Leadership\nA born leader who likes doing things your way and how you see fit. You want to be in charge as the one giving the orders, instead of taking them. Leadership positions come naturally as you thrive under pressure and take responsibility well.\n\n### Independent\nYou want to be independent and in charge of your own life - where you can make your own decisions and not have to answer to anybody else. Being a follower and co-dependant does not work for you long term.\n\n### Ambitious\nAmbitious and driven, you are always looking for the next project to work on and don't take no for an answer. You feel alive by taking action and going forward instead of being passive and holding back. Stressful situations bring out the best in you.\n\n### Argumentative\nAs a 1 lifepath you love to argue - you do it for sport. Debating and going back and forth with people is extremely entertaining for 1s and they love it. In fact a 1 lifepath will often argue back even if they know they are wrong. You keep it real and say things how they are which often leads to conflict and people getting offended.\n\n### Competitive\nYou embody a competitive drive that always wants to be the first in everything you do. The element of competition often brings out the best in you as falling second is not something you are interested in.\n\n### Athlete\n1 Lifepaths are amongst the best athletes due to their naturally athletic build and a competitive mindset. Physical activities and working out is highly recommended as this burns off your emotional energy and makes you more balanced and calm. 1 Lifepaths don't just work out for their health - they do it for the mind.\n\n### Stress\nYou can handle stress and pressure extremely well - you thrive when others might fold. In fact you will perform the best with your back against the wall and all odds against you.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n1s win at life by being a leader doing things your way and standing independent. True fulfillment comes from being in charge of your own path and even if you fail the victory is that you did it on your terms.\n\n### Challenges\n1s fail at life by avoiding courage when it is your moment to step up and lead. If fear keeps you from doing the right thing and you lower your head to follow the crowd you miss your soul mission as a 1 lifepath.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 7 Life Path = 79%: Independent intellect and leadership align through mutual respect and space.\n- 11 Life Path = 79%: The leader and the visionary find equal footing when ego is set aside.\n- 1 Life Path = 76%: Shared drive creates momentum, though ego competition is constant.\n- 28 Life Path = 66%: Two independent leaders navigating their paths with karmic awareness.\n- 8 Life Path = 65%: Ambition and power align, though control dynamics can create friction.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 9 Life Path = 14%: The mirror absorbs the 1's leadership energy without giving direction back.\n- 4 Life Path = 48%: Two disciplined energies, but fundamentally different approaches to life.\n- 5 Life Path = 51%: Freedom resists the 1's need to lead and control outcomes.\n- 3 Life Path = 53%: Social energy dilutes the 1's focused and independent drive.\n- 6 Life Path = 53%: The nurturer's group focus conflicts with the 1's need for independence.\n- 33 Life Path = 50%: Two powerful influences competing for direction and authority.\n- 22 Life Path = 59%: Both builders, but the 22's collective vision clashes with the 1's ego.`,\n        3: `# Three Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to communicate and express creativity. With a strong connection to your inner child, you love to laugh, joke and have a great sense of humor. The social aspect of life is very important to you - your friends are like your family.\n\nMultitasking is your talent but you can struggle from a short attention span and have trouble focusing - you are good at starting things but not that good at finishing them.\n\nCommunication is your biggest skillset and key to success, whether that is through talking, writing or posting online.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Social\nYou are a social person who loves to talk, communicate and embrace the social aspect of this world. Your friends are like family to you and maintaining a strong social life is key for your well being. Socializing and making new friends is how you recharge. The lack of social life can make you feel drained.\n\n### Network\nYour network is your networth. For you it's not just about what you know - it's about who you know. The more connections you make the easier life becomes.\n\n### Short Attention Span\nYou have a short attention span and get easily sidetracked, you will often find yourself struggling to focus on one thing at a time and need to switch things up to keep you interested.\n\n### Comedy\nYou have a great sense of humor, you love jokes and pranks and anything that you deem to be funny - often finding yourself in the role of the jokester within the friend group. Laughter is your best medicine.\n\n### Communication\nCommunication is your biggest gift as a 3 lifepath. Expressing your thoughts and sharing a message with the world comes naturally to you. Whether its through talking, writing or posting on social media - find out what works for you and go with it.\n\n### Multitask\nYou are a master at multitasking who can easily work on 10 different things at the same time. Having different options to choose from is key as you need to switch things up to keep you interested.\n\n### Luck\n3 is the luckiest number in numerology - being at the right place at the right time is often the shortcut to success for 3 lifepaths.\n\n### Creative\nYou are a very creative person with many bright ideas and you love to express yourself through creative outlets.\n\n### Fun\n3 Lifepaths need to have fun in life. All work and no play makes jack a dull boy. You need time to have fun, socialize and entertain yourself. Boredom and burnout are some of the biggest enemies.\n\n### Childlike\nYou have a strong connection to your inner child that will never truly grow up, no matter how old you are. You want to laugh, joke, have fun and not take anything too serious.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\nThrees win at life by being a master networker who knows a guy for everything, by taking the role of the middleman and bringing people together. Communication is the foundation of all that you do.\n\n### Challenges\nThrees fail by not finishing what they start. Bright ideas come easily but without focus and discipline they never reach their full potential. Distraction and lack of follow-through keep you from building the success your creativity is capable of producing.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 5 Life Path = 83%: Communication and freedom create a vibrant, adventurous bond built on movement and expression.\n- 8 Life Path = 80%: Social networking meets business power — a productive and dynamic combination.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 66%: Shared humor and creativity keep the energy light and entertaining.\n- 6 Life Path = 66%: Social warmth and nurturing energy find easy common ground.\n- 11 Life Path = 66%: Both expressive and passionate, though emotional depth differs.\n- 33 Life Path = 66%: Two communicators with creative purpose and shared frequency.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 4 Life Path = 17%: Structure and spontaneity create constant friction — order vs. chaos.\n- 22 Life Path = 17%: Playfulness clashes with serious legacy-building ambitions.\n- 9 Life Path = 52%: Both social, but ego and surface adaptation create disconnect.\n- 7 Life Path = 51%: Extroversion meets solitude — fundamentally opposing life needs.\n- 1 Life Path = 53%: Leadership and communication compete rather than complement.\n- 28 Life Path = 53%: Karmic weight and social lightness rarely find alignment.`,\n        4: `# Four Life Path\n\nYou are here to work and build yourself up.\n\nHard working and disciplined - you outwork others to get ahead and use consistency to your advantage. You are organized and like being in control. While others take risks, you build a steady foundation - slow and steady wins the race is the mindset that suits you best. Routines are your friend but it's easy to get stuck within a \"system\" that doesn't serve you best.\n\nYour work ethic is your biggest strength - you have always had to work hard for everything you have and this is what made you who you are.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Work\nYou are a hard working person who always gives 110% with everything they do. Building a strong work ethic is part of your soul mission and your key to success. You have to work hard on everything you do because nothing will come easy - if you want something, be ready to work for it. Laziness is your biggest enemy.\n\n### Organized\nYou are very good at organizing, whether it's your belongings in the house, files on your computer or documents at your work place. Putting \"everything in its right place\" comes naturally to you.\n\n### Career\nCareer is very important for 4 lifepaths and they often define themselves through their work. Having a job or a project you can work on every day is key - without it you will not feel complete.\n\n### Systematic\nYou have a systematic approach to life and operate best within a controlled environment. You have a strong mind for understanding operations and systems. Chaos and uncertainty is your biggest enemy.\n\n### Disciplined\nDisciplined and structured, your mindset and willpower is the driving force behind your actions. A 4 lifepath will never get far without discipline.\n\n### Control\nYou need to know where you are going and what you are working towards. Without control, a 4 lifepath is left at the mercy of chaos and uncertainty.\n\n### Overly Serious\nFun is not your default mode. You are often mistaken for cold, but in reality, you are focused on what matters most.\n\n### Too Rigid\nChange feels like disorder to you, but flexibility is not weakness - it is the strength that keeps what you've built from breaking.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n4s win at life through steady effort and consistent routines built around a clear vision of your goals. By giving 110 percent to everything you do you turn discipline and work ethic into your greatest strength.\n\n### Challenges\n4s fail by falling into laziness and wasting time on what does not matter. When effort is avoided the 4 lifepath quickly spirals into frustration and stagnation.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 33 Life Path = 76%: Disciplined effort supports the master teacher's long-term structured vision.\n- 8 Life Path = 75%: Both hardworking and results-driven — mutual respect flows naturally.\n- 22 Life Path = 70%: Two builders who understand the deep value of slow and steady effort.\n- 4 Life Path = 69%: Shared work ethic and structure, though rigid energy can stall progress.\n- 7 Life Path = 68%: Systematic thinking meets knowledge-seeking in a compatible order.\n- 6 Life Path = 65%: Both responsible and structured in how they approach life and family.\n- 28 Life Path = 62%: Two disciplined energies navigating karmic tests with shared patience.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 17%: Creative chaos disrupts the 4's essential need for order and routine.\n- 5 Life Path = 25%: Freedom and routine are fundamentally and permanently opposed.\n- 11 Life Path = 57%: Emotional volatility unsettles the 4's carefully structured world.\n- 1 Life Path = 48%: Both want control, but leadership styles constantly clash.\n- 9 Life Path = 48%: Adaptive mirror energy confuses the systematic 4 lifepath.`,\n        5: `# 5 Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to move, change and evolve. Free spirited and open minded - the only constant in your life is change. You chase new places, ideas, energies and people and evolve yourself through your experiences. Being stagnant in one place affects you negatively - you do not do well living in a routine and feeling like you're stuck in the system. You need to experience change and motion to be happy. Charismatic and charming - you are a natural entertainer and good at keeping people company. Your heart craves adventure and excitement.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Travel\nYou love to travel and explore new places - your soul urges you to travel to foreign lands and experience different cultures and ways of life. The more you travel the better you feel.\n\n### Freedom\nYou are a free spirit at heart who does not want to be tied down and stuck within a system. Freedom is a necessity for you that must never be compromised.\n\n### Change\nYou need constant change in life - stepping out of the routines and being spontaneous is necessary for a healthy mindset. Being stagnant and feeling stuck is your worst enemy.\n\n### Attract\n5 lifepaths often find themselves grabbing attention from the opposite sex wherever they go. People are naturally attracted to the 5 energy and often gravitate towards their flirty energy.\n\n### Entertainer\nYou are a natural entertainer who can easily keep people company. \"The heart of the party\" who makes sure everybody is having a good time.\n\n### Indecisive\nDecision making is not your strength and you can often come off as being indecisive. You often feel like being pulled from two sides, unsure which way to go.\n\n### Beauty\n5 is the number of the Model and Good Looks - often heralded for their natural beauty, 5 lifepaths dominate the modeling and acting industry.\n\n### Open Minded\nYou are an open minded person who is always interested in learning different topics, subjects and beliefs.\n\n### Active\nYou love an active lifestyle of going places, doing things and feeling a sense of adventure, even in your everyday life.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n5s win at life by traveling widely and expanding their horizon. You gather new ideas, skillsets, connections and knowledge from every experience and turn them into advantages that keep you moving forward.\n\n### Challenges\n5s often fail through relationships with the opposite sex. The freedom of 5 allows you to attract many options but not every option is meant for you. Choose relationships with care.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 83%: Freedom and communication create non-stop adventure, fun, and shared expression.\n- 7 Life Path = 81%: Exploration meets knowledge — two independent souls in deep mutual expansion.\n- 6 Life Path = 80%: Freedom and nurturing balance beautifully when both are willing to commit.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 8 Life Path = 66%: Dynamic energy meets business power — exciting and fast-moving.\n- 9 Life Path = 66%: Both adaptive and movement-oriented — a natural and easy flow.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 33 Life Path = 17%: The gravity of the master teacher conflicts deeply with the 5's need for freedom.\n- 22 Life Path = 24%: Legacy-building structures constrain the 5's need to roam and explore.\n- 4 Life Path = 25%: Routine is the 5's greatest enemy — this pairing drains both sides.\n- 5 Life Path = 52%: Two free spirits can scatter in all directions without any grounding.\n- 11 Life Path = 52%: Emotional intensity clashes with the 5's preference to keep things light.\n- 28 Life Path = 55%: Karmic weight slows the 5's forward momentum significantly.\n- 1 Life Path = 51%: Independence vs. independence — both want to go their own way.`,\n        6: `# 6 Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to protect, provide and nurture. Loyal and helpful - you love to take care and look after those around you. You take responsibility seriously and can always be counted on to show up and that's why people trust you. You spend a lot of time at home and prefer family time and stability over uncertainty and chaos. A sense of community and belonging is essential.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Family\nThe family aspect is very important for you. Your life will largely revolve around your family and the people closest to you. Building your own family is one of your soul missions.\n\n### Home\nYour home is your castle, your safe space and the most important place for you. You love that comfortable feeling of being in your own element and can turn any house into a home.\n\n### Helpful\nYou are naturally a very helpful person, love taking care of others and will never turn your back on a friend in need.\n\n### Outside the Box\nYou have a unique perspective to life and can find angles that others might miss - seeing the bigger picture and thinking outside the box is what you do best.\n\n### Responsible\nYou take responsibility very seriously and will go out of your way to fulfill your duties. You can always be counted on, even if it means going through difficulties.\n\n### Nurturer\nIntuitive nurturer and caretaker - you love to serve and be of use to your close ones. True happiness comes from making others around you happy.\n\n### Loyal\nYou are an extremely loyal and trustworthy person. Loyalty is part of your core values and you need others around you to match that loyalty.\n\n### Real Estate\n6 Lifepaths do well with real estate, whether it's selling houses, flipping them, fixing them or designing them.\n\n### Building the Bloodline\n6 Lifepaths are meant to work together with their family and build each other up. Family businesses, projects and endeavors - keeping each other close and working together is key.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n6s win at life through the people around you. Success comes from working together, building others up and benefitting from their growth. You are not meant to do everything alone.\n\n### Challenges\n6s fail by becoming overly selfish and falling into a service-to-self mindset. Independence and personal identity are important but when success comes at the expense of those you care about the 6 lifepath loses its true purpose.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 5 Life Path = 80%: Freedom's spark lights up the loyal 6's need for warmth and shared experience.\n- 8 Life Path = 80%: Nurturer meets power — a strong, balanced team that builds together.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 66%: Social warmth and communication fill the 6's need for community and belonging.\n- 4 Life Path = 65%: Both responsible and home-oriented — a reliable and grounded alignment.\n- 22 Life Path = 65%: Family legacy and community-building values find strong common ground.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 9 Life Path = 10%: Deepest conflict — the mirror absorbs the 6's nurturing energy without reciprocation.\n- 7 Life Path = 36%: Solitude clashes deeply with the 6's need for closeness and community.\n- 6 Life Path = 59%: Too much of the same nurturing energy creates codependency and stagnation.\n- 11 Life Path = 59%: Emotional volatility disrupts the stable, caring home the 6 works to build.\n- 33 Life Path = 59%: The master teacher's world-changing intensity overwhelms the nurturing 6.\n- 1 Life Path = 53%: Independence clashes with the 6's deep need for togetherness and loyalty.\n- 28 Life Path = 53%: Karmic cycles bring instability that the 6 cannot consistently support.`,\n        7: `# Seven Life Path\n\n## Primary Energy\n\nYou are here to gain knowledge, evolve the mind and teach it to others. Your mind is your weapon and learning is how you sharpen it - by absorbing knowledge and seeking truth is how you progress the most in life. An intelligent mind often finds themselves in solitude and you can easily feel misunderstood by your peers and struggle to fit in.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Intelligence\nYou are intelligent, smart and your brain works quick. You can easily figure out subjects and difficult concepts other people struggle to comprehend. Decoding and problem solving is fun for you as your brain needs constant stimulation and challenges.\n\n### Knowledge\nKnowledge is what you crave and gaining new information is how you feed that hunger. You love to learn, study and research all sorts of different subjects.\n\n### Loner\nAt heart, you spend a lot of time by yourself and don't mind solitude - in fact you prefer it. Whenever you are social you need to spend some time alone to recharge that social battery.\n\n### Master of Occult\n7s are the best when it comes to esoteric teachings such as numerology, astrology and other forms of imprinted energy. You are a natural at this.\n\n### Relationships\nMaintaining a relationship can be difficult for a 7 lifepath and they often find themselves spending a large part of their life alone. You struggle with expressing your emotions and feelings to your partner.\n\n### Misunderstood\n7 lifepaths frequently feel misunderstood by their peers due to their high intelligence and unique perspectives. You break the mold that most people try to fit in.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n7s win at life by constantly learning and staying aligned with new discoveries, inventions and progress of any kind. The moment you stop feeding your mind with knowledge and curiosity is the moment you begin to fall behind.\n\n### Challenges\n7s fail at life by closing the mind and rejecting spiritual growth. If you refuse to study and instead try to live exactly as everyone else you will not progress far.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 28 Life Path = 83%: Knowledge meets karmic mastery — the deepest and most aligned pairing for the 7.\n- 5 Life Path = 81%: Freedom and knowledge go perfectly hand in hand through exploration.\n- 11 Life Path = 81%: Two spiritual seekers with profound intuitive and emotional understanding.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 1 Life Path = 79%: Both independent thinkers who deeply respect each other's autonomous space.\n- 22 Life Path = 69%: The builder and the seeker find a productive, long-term partnership.\n- 4 Life Path = 68%: Systematic thinking complements the 7's love of deep knowledge.\n- 7 Life Path = 60%: Two loners who understand each other perfectly without needing words.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 8 Life Path = 18%: Material power and wealth-focus conflict with the 7's spiritual pursuits.\n- 33 Life Path = 24%: Master teacher and deep seeker clash over method and approach to truth.\n- 6 Life Path = 36%: Community expectations clash with the 7's fundamental need for solitude.\n- 9 Life Path = 43%: Ego and surface adaptation disrupt the 7's focused inner world.\n- 3 Life Path = 51%: Constant socializing overwhelms the 7's need for quiet and reflection.`,\n        8: `# 8 Lifepath\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are destined for power and abundance through karmic balance. Money will always play a big role in your life, whether it's about having it or not having it - you are good at making money, also very good at losing money, because 8 lifepaths are meant to experience both sides of life. Look at the shape of 8 - what goes around, comes around. Finding balance within is the key for your success. Karma also plays a big role in your life and often dictates which side of the 8 energy you get to experience.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Money\nYou don't just want money, you need it. You want to understand how it works, grows and scales and eventually build a system that generates income with your name on it. Business and finances come naturally to you.\n\n### Karma\nYou are a karmic soul - if you create unbalance by stealing or hurting others unrighteously, it will come back to you 10 times like a boomerang. You have to live a righteous and balanced life if you want to be successful as an 8 lifepath.\n\n### Power\n8 lifepaths embody a natural instinct towards power and they do well with it. You will often gravitate towards people within positions of power and places of great influence.\n\n### Yin/Yang\nIn many ways the 8 energy represents the balance of the Yin and the Yang - there is no black without white, darkness without light, or happiness without sadness. Finding balance in everything is key.\n\n### Risktaker\n8 Lifepaths thrive in risky situations and often get powered by the idea of going ALL-IN. Risk management is key as building yourself up slow and steady yields more consistent results.\n\n### Easy Come Easy Go\n8 Lifepaths are good at making money, also good at losing money. Fast rise to success is often followed by an even quicker downfall.\n\n### Balance\n8 Lifepaths tend to always swing between extremes. Finding balance within all equations builds a sustainable system and avoids burnout.\n\n### Material Side\n8 is a very materialistic number and acts as a building block for the material side of life. Achieving materialistic success through financial and monetary means is a great goal to have.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n8s win through a system of Equal Energy Exchange where people give you money or other forms of value and get something in return. Only when everyone benefits from the trade and both sides are satisfied are you able to scale it efficiently.\n\n### Challenges\n8s fail at life by cheating, stealing, manipulating or moving in unrighteous ways. Karma returns quickly and if you create imbalance you will face heavy payback. Every action carries weight and even the smallest dishonesty triggers consequences.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 80%: Social networking meets business power — an unbeatable wealth-building combination.\n- 6 Life Path = 80%: Provider energy and nurturer energy create a strong, abundant team.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 4 Life Path = 75%: Both hardworking and results-driven — a strong and reliable business pairing.\n- 28 Life Path = 69%: Two karma-and-power-driven energies that resonate on a deep level.\n- 1 Life Path = 65%: Ambition and power align well through shared drive and mutual respect.\n- 5 Life Path = 66%: Business energy and freedom can create fast-moving dynamic momentum.\n- 22 Life Path = 66%: Two material builders working together toward something lasting.\n- 33 Life Path = 66%: Power meets influence — a commanding and capable pairing.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 7 Life Path = 18%: Material wealth and power conflict with the 7's spiritual detachment.\n- 8 Life Path = 31%: Two 8s create karmic imbalance — too much concentrated power in one place.\n- 9 Life Path = 52%: The mirror of ego meets the force of 8 — a volatile and unstable mix.\n- 11 Life Path = 52%: Emotional fire and material focus pull in opposite directions.`,\n        9: `# 9 Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to reflect and adapt. Extremely adaptive - you can fit into anywhere and go along with new situations. You pick up qualities from those around you and match their energy - like a mirror. Your environment and the people around you have a huge influence on your life. You prefer working from behind the scenes over being in the spotlight and perform better in a team than alone.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Adapt\nYou will adapt to your current environment and do it well. This can be your biggest strength or biggest weakness as you can adapt equally to success and failure. Being around good people will boost you up as being around negativity will drag you down.\n\n### Environment\nEnvironment plays a huge role to who you are as a person. You can never be the best version of yourself living in a bad environment. Where you live, where you work, where you spend the most time - all have a huge effect on your overall energy.\n\n### Reverse Engineer\nReverse engineering is one of your biggest skills - you don't need to invent new things yourself, you can just take something and make it better. Perfecting existing concepts is what you are best at.\n\n### Ego\nYou have a strong ego and a powerful self image, make sure to back it up with results and not let ego get bigger than yourself.\n\n### Smart\nIntelligent and observant, you learn fast and easily pick up new subjects and teachings. Your mind works quickly. You can be a great strategist working from behind the scenes.\n\n### Appearance\nGood looks are of great value to you - you appreciate style, beauty and nice looking things and the people around you.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 5 Life Path = 66%: Both adaptive and experience-oriented — a natural and easy mutual flow.\n- 22 Life Path = 66%: The mirror absorbs the builder's vision and helps amplify it outward.\n- 33 Life Path = 66%: Adaptation serves the master teacher's mission with natural flexibility.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 1 Life Path = 14%: The mirror reflects leadership energy back but creates no real traction.\n- 6 Life Path = 10%: Deepest conflict — the nurturer gives freely while the mirror only absorbs.\n- 11 Life Path = 17%: Emotional passion collides with cold adaptive energy — a painful mismatch.\n- 28 Life Path = 18%: Karmic depth and surface-level adaptation simply cannot coexist.\n- 3 Life Path = 52%: Social energy and adaptation create surface connection but no real depth.\n- 8 Life Path = 52%: Power and the mirror create an unbalanced and exhausting exchange.\n- 4 Life Path = 48%: Structure frustrates the ever-shifting and adaptive 9.\n- 9 Life Path = 45%: Two mirrors reflecting each other leads nowhere and builds nothing.\n- 7 Life Path = 43%: Deep knowledge-seeking and ego adaptation rarely align in purpose.`,\n        11: `# 11 Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nEmotional and passionate, you are an old soul with intuition and deeper understanding of reality. You feel a strong sense of mission to change the world and help make it a better place. Your emotional energy is intense - you feel things at a higher level and often struggle to find the balance within.\n\nYou have very good intuition and should always listen to your heart - chasing your passion works best as you won't be happy doing work you are not passionate about.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Emotional\nControl your emotions and don't let them control you. Making impulsive and heated decisions often leads to mistakes. You need to balance and channel your emotional energy into something productive.\n\n### Charisma\nWhen you speak, people listen. When you step into the room, people notice. The 11 energy just grabs attention and works well with the spotlight and you can use this to your advantage in many aspects of life.\n\n### Old Soul\nYou have known things before and often gravitate towards people older than you as friends. This is the Old Soul quality of an 11 as you have been through many reincarnations before.\n\n### Drive\nYou are extremely driven towards your goals. When you set your mind to something, you will see it done.\n\n### Visionary\nYou are a master visionary who imagines the world they want to be in and moves towards that reality. You see the best in people and guide them towards reaching their full potential.\n\n### Intuition\nYou have an intuition like none other, you feel things, know things, predict things - often feeling guided by your higher self towards the right things. This is your gift so have faith in it.\n\n### Spiritual\nYou are deeply spiritual and often gravitate towards higher knowledge - such as numerology, astrology and esoteric knowledge.\n\n### Duality\n11 lifepaths often have two sides to them. One side is wonderful and charismatic - the other side can be volatile and destructive. The biggest sign of an unbalanced 11 is you never know which version you will get.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n11s win at life by discovering what you love above all else and committing fully to it. Until you find that passion you will always feel incomplete.\n\n### Challenges\n11s face tests and challenges and are pushed to the limits of their emotional capabilities by the universe as a test to see how balanced they are. You have difficult challenges because that's what you signed up for as an 11.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 28 Life Path = 83%: Emotional depth and karmic power resonate at the highest level of alignment.\n- 7 Life Path = 81%: Spiritual intuition meets deep knowledge — a profound and rare connection.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 1 Life Path = 79%: Strong leadership energy that respects the 11's visionary presence.\n- 3 Life Path = 66%: Both expressive and passionate — communication finds an easy outlet.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 9 Life Path = 17%: Ego-driven adaptation wounds the 11's deep emotional and spiritual world.\n- 22 Life Path = 59%: Builder energy cannot match or contain the 11's emotional intensity.\n- 6 Life Path = 59%: Nurturing expectations create pressure that the 11's volatility breaks.\n- 11 Life Path = 59%: Two 11s can amplify each other's emotional extremes to a dangerous level.\n- 4 Life Path = 57%: The 4's need for order is constantly disrupted by the 11's emotional waves.\n- 8 Life Path = 52%: Material focus cannot hold the spiritual fire and depth of the 11.\n- 33 Life Path = 52%: Two old souls, but the 11's volatility disrupts the 33's steady mission.\n- 5 Life Path = 52%: Free-spirit energy lacks the emotional depth the 11 deeply craves.`,\n        22: `# 22 Life Path\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to build a legacy. 22 represents the highest aspect of the material side of life and it is part of your soul mission to develop it - visualizing a better world of tomorrow and moving towards that reality. You are good at building up other people and bringing out the best in them. You work hard and do what has to be done, no matter what it takes.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Master Builder\nYour job is to build things of your own, whether it's building a company, a business, a family, building up other people - do it yourself and do it authentically so it is something you can be proud of.\n\n### Master Destroyer\n22s have the ability to master destroy the old, as it is needed to build the new. Breaking down old barriers and generational blockages so you can heal and build a better future.\n\n### Make Those Around Better\nYou are best at building up other people, taking somebody and making them successful. You are often better at building up and doing things for others, than you are for yourself.\n\n### Ends Justify the Means\nYou are results oriented and relentless in working towards your goals. You are not afraid to do what it takes to get there, even if it means sacrifice for the greater good.\n\n### Old Soul\nYou are an old soul who will constantly be tested in life. The challenges you have to pass will be much harder than most other people. With more potential comes more challenges.\n\n### Materialistic\n22 is a materialistic number, you are here to embrace and build up this aspect of life. Making money and reaching abundance is a great goal.\n\n### Following\nYou are naturally talented at building a following - people are inclined to follow your lead and look up to you for guidance.\n\n### Strategy\nAs a master strategist, you are a capable planner and are able to think 10 steps ahead. You turn chaos into structure and uncertainty into a master plan.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n22s win at life by building something of your own whether it is a business, a project or a brand. If you can claim it as your own and take pride in the authenticity of your achievement then you are on the right path.\n\n### Challenges\n22s fail by neglecting the material side of life. False teachings that dismiss money and possessions lead you off course because your path requires resources. As a master builder you are meant to take material means and direct them toward the greater good.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 33 Life Path = 80%: Two master numbers aligned on legacy, influence, and building a better world.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 4 Life Path = 70%: Shared work ethic and systematic thinking — a naturally productive pairing.\n- 22 Life Path = 70%: Two builders who see the same long-term vision and amplify each other.\n- 7 Life Path = 69%: Strategy meets deep knowledge in a powerful and disciplined partnership.\n- 8 Life Path = 66%: Two material-world forces building something lasting with complementary power.\n- 9 Life Path = 66%: The adaptive mirror serves the builder's vision effectively and broadly.\n- 6 Life Path = 65%: Family legacy and community-building values align with the 22's mission.\n- 28 Life Path = 63%: Karmic cycles support and deepen the 22's long-term legacy work.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 3 Life Path = 17%: Social distraction and lightness consistently undermine serious legacy-building.\n- 5 Life Path = 24%: Freedom resists the 22's disciplined, structured long-term plans entirely.\n- 11 Life Path = 59%: Emotional intensity disrupts the methodical pace of the master builder.\n- 1 Life Path = 59%: Independence conflicts with the 22's collective and community-focused mission.`,\n        28: `# 28/1 Life Path\n\n## Primary Energy\n\n28/1 is a powerful combination — the ambition and independence of the 1 lifepath channeled through the karmic, wealth-oriented energy of 28. You are here to lead and build, but your journey will test you through cycles of rise and fall before you reach lasting success.\n\nThe number 28 always reduces to 1 (2+8=10, 1+0=1), meaning your core destiny is leadership and independence. But the path to get there carries the karmic weight of the 2 and the 8 — balance, relationships, power, and the consequences of your actions.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Leadership\nLike all 1 lifepaths, you are here to lead on your own terms. You are driven, independent, and unwilling to follow others for long. You are at your best when you are the one setting the direction.\n\n### Karma\nThe 8 in your number means karma plays a significant role in your life. What you put out comes back to you — treat others as you wish to be treated, and your path will remain clear.\n\n### Power and Cycles\nYou are likely to experience significant highs and lows throughout your life. These cycles are part of your soul journey. Each fall is meant to teach you something before the next rise.\n\n### Drive\nYour willpower is exceptional. You do not give up easily and are capable of rebuilding from scratch when necessary.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n28/1s win at life by combining the courage to act independently with the wisdom that comes from karmic experience. When you lead with integrity, your influence and success compound over time.\n\n### Challenges\n28/1s face challenges when ego overrides judgment or when shortcuts tempt you away from doing things the right way. The karmic nature of 28 means unrighteous actions create swift and heavy consequences.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 7 Life Path = 83%: Deep knowledge and karmic mastery — the most spiritually aligned pairing for 28.\n- 11 Life Path = 83%: Emotional depth and karmic power resonate at a profound and rare level.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 28 Life Path = 70%: Shared karmic cycles create deep mutual understanding and rare trust.\n- 8 Life Path = 69%: Two power-and-karma-driven energies that amplify each other's strength.\n- 1 Life Path = 66%: Independent leadership supports the 28's karmic mission with drive.\n- 22 Life Path = 63%: Builder and karmic master align on long-term goals and shared purpose.\n- 4 Life Path = 62%: Discipline and karmic work ethic find steady and reliable common ground.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 9 Life Path = 18%: The surface mirror cannot hold the deep karmic weight of the 28 path.\n- 3 Life Path = 53%: Social lightness clashes with the weight and depth of karmic lessons.\n- 6 Life Path = 53%: Nurturing comfort cannot provide what deep karmic growth requires.\n- 33 Life Path = 53%: Two master frequencies on different wavelengths — misaligned paths.\n- 5 Life Path = 55%: Freedom avoids the heavy karmic responsibility the 28 must embrace.`,\n        33: `# 33 Lifepath\n\n## Primary & Secondary Energy\n\n### Primary\nYou are here to teach, influence and change the world. 33 is the highest frequency and the rarest lifepath in numerology. You have been trusted with the daunting task of influencing the world. You have limitless potential but also the hardest challenges. Life is not meant to be easy for you as you face constant pushback and failures, but nothing you can't overcome.\n\n## Characteristics\n\n### Master Teacher\nWise beyond the years, you carry a deep level of understanding of reality with knowledge not gained from books but from experience of the soul. You feel a duty to share your wisdom with the world.\n\n### Influence\nThe energy of influence follows you wherever you go. Anything you do will pick up traction, people you put attention to start doing good and projects you work on start to thrive.\n\n### Trailblazer\nYou are not here to follow somebody else's road, you are here to carve out your own path. Doing things nobody else has done before and taking the road less traveled.\n\n### Old Soul\n33 is the oldest soul within the reincarnation cycle. You have amazing intuition and a 6th sense for predicting outcomes and seeing into the future.\n\n### Big Ego, Big Standard\nYou hold high expectations - for yourself and others. But unchecked, that ego isolates you. Stay humble to stay impactful.\n\n### Karma Closer\nYou're here to complete the karmic cycle. This may be your final lifetime in this realm if you stay aligned.\n\n### Amplify\n33 Energy amplifies others around them. You can bring out the best in people, you can bring out the worst in people. Choose who you give your energy to carefully.\n\n## Strengths & Challenges\n\n### Strengths\n33s success is measured by the influence you leave at the end of the road. The true question is how much impact you were able to have on this earth in your lifetime.\n\n### Challenges\nAs a 33 lifepath, life is not meant to be easy for you. People will fight back at you, people will try to stop you from reaching your potential. This is a test by the universe - never let anybody's opinion or actions stop you from reaching your goals.\n\n## Friendly Numbers\n- 22 Life Path = 80%: Two master numbers united on legacy, influence, and elevating the world.\n\n## Neutral Numbers\n- 4 Life Path = 76%: Disciplined structure gives the 33's broad vision a foundation to stand on.\n- 3 Life Path = 66%: Communication energy amplifies and spreads the 33's teaching mission.\n- 8 Life Path = 66%: Power and influence create a commanding and impactful partnership.\n- 9 Life Path = 66%: The adaptive mirror reflects and broadcasts the 33's message at scale.\n\n## Enemy Numbers\n- 5 Life Path = 17%: The need for freedom and lightness resists the gravity of the master teacher.\n- 7 Life Path = 24%: Solitary knowledge-seeking conflicts with the 33's large-scale influence mission.\n- 1 Life Path = 50%: Independent ego competes with the 33's collective and world-serving purpose.\n- 33 Life Path = 52%: Two 33s amplify each other's challenges more than their strengths.\n- 11 Life Path = 52%: Both are old souls, but the 11's volatility disrupts the 33's steady mission.\n- 28 Life Path = 53%: Two karmic masters operating on different frequencies and timelines.\n- 6 Life Path = 59%: The nurturing focus of 6 cannot contain the 33's world-changing mission.`\n    },\n    zodiac: {\n        \"Rat\": `# The Rat\nThe first sign: Rats are intelligent, strategic, and survival-oriented operators. As the first sign, they lead through awareness, persuasion, and rapid pattern recognition, often guiding outcomes from behind the scenes.\n\nIntelligent: Processes information quickly and solves problems with minimal resources. Excels under pressure by adapting strategy in real time rather than relying on fixed plans.\n\nInstinctive: Reads environments quickly and reacts before threats fully surface. Decisions are driven by gut assessment backed by pattern recognition rather than hesitation.\n\nCharming & Social: Naturally builds networks and influences outcomes through social access. Charisma is used strategically to open doors and gather information.\n\nSecretive: Prefers operating behind the scenes and controlling information flow. This creates strategic advantage but limits transparency with others.\n\nManipulative: Subtly guides situations to personal advantage without drawing attention. Influence is applied quietly, reducing open conflict while steering outcomes.\n\nProtective, Best Parents: Strongly prioritizes family and offspring. Creates security through vigilance, planning, and constant involvement in loved ones' well-being.\n\nInfluential During Crises: Steps into coordination roles when pressure is high. Organizes people and systems quietly, restoring order through strategy rather than visibility.\n\n## Strengths\n- Sharp Thinker\n- Strategic Leader\n- Persuasive Communicator\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Rat vs Ox = 105%: Strategic intelligence aligns with trust, creating long term coordination.\n- Rat vs Dragon = 80%: Strategic intelligence supports authority without direct challenge.\n- Rat vs Monkey = 80%: Strategic intelligence aligns, allowing optimization without power struggle.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Rat vs Rat = 70%: Shared intelligence and secrecy create function, though trust is carefully managed.\n- Rat vs Snake = 70%: Strategy and intuition combine, but secrecy limits transparency.\n- Rat vs Cat = 50%: Both operate strategically but hidden manipulation reduces trust.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Rat vs Horse = 10%: Independent action clashes with covert manipulation, causing breakdown in trust.`,\n        \"Ox\": `# The Ox\nThe 2nd sign: Oxen represent endurance, reliability, and long-term strength. As the second sign, they build what others start, turning effort into stability through persistence and consistency.\n\nPatient: Maintains composure under pressure and resists rushed decisions. Progress is made through steady assessment and endurance rather than speed.\n\nStubborn: Holds position firmly once decided. Determination sustains long-term effort but reduces flexibility when compromise is required.\n\nAuthoritative: Naturally takes charge and establishes order. Authority is expressed calmly through structure, consistency, and expectation setting.\n\nDetermined: Maintains unwavering persistence toward goals. Progress continues through resistance and delay without abandoning course.\n\n## Strengths\n- Reliability\n- Patience\n- Endurance\n- Consistency\n- Authority\n\n## Challenges\n- Stubborn\n- Domineering Under Pressure\n- Rigid Thinking\n- Resistant to Change\n\nHealth and Wellness: Naturally physically robust but prone to stiffness or overexertion if rest and recovery are neglected.\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Ox vs Rat = 105%: Strategic intelligence aligns with trust, creating strong coordination.\n- Ox vs Rooster = 80%: Reliability and enforcement align, producing disciplined cooperation.\n- Ox vs Snake = 80%: Stability and intuition combine, allowing steady and strategic progress.\n- Ox vs Ox = 70%: Shared endurance and loyalty create strong foundations, though rigidity must be managed.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Ox vs Cat = 60%: Mental agility meets rigid stability.\n- Ox vs Dog = 60%: Loyalty aligns, but emotional expression remains limited.\n- Ox vs Horse = 60%: Endurance and independence coexist, but timing and pace often clash.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Ox vs Goat = 10%: Rigid stability suppresses flexibility and harmony, causing cooperation to break down.`,\n        \"Tiger\": `# The Tiger\nThe third sign: Tigers are bold, physically powerful, and action-driven. As the third sign, they bring momentum, courage, and decisive force where movement and leadership are required.\n\nBrave and Confident: Approaches obstacles directly without hesitation. Confidence comes from action rather than planning, often inspiring others to move when situations feel uncertain.\n\nUnpredictable and Impulsive: Acts quickly and decisively, often without full assessment. Momentum creates wins, but impulsiveness can also create avoidable setbacks.\n\nTough: Physically and emotionally resilient. Handles adversity without retreat and remains functional under prolonged stress.\n\nRebellious: Challenges authority and established norms. Innovation is driven by resistance to limits, often creating friction with structure.\n\nAffectionate: Expresses warmth and emotional closeness toward loved ones.\n\n## Strengths\n- Brave\n- Fiercely Independent\n- Physically Powerful\n- Mentally Tough\n- Naturally Generous\n\nHealth & Wellness: Naturally fit and physically resilient. Primary risk is burnout, injury, or exhaustion from sustained high-output behavior.\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Tiger vs Tiger = 100%: Shared intensity and freedom-driven momentum create strong alignment.\n- Tiger vs Dog = 80%: Tiger supplies drive while Dog commits through loyalty once trust is earned.\n- Tiger vs Horse = 80%: Shared vitality and endurance fuel momentum.\n- Tiger vs Pig = 80%: Intensity and enjoyment coexist, creating attraction without control struggle.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Tiger vs Cat = 70%: Cat tempers risk through observation while Tiger pushes momentum.\n- Tiger vs Dragon = 60%: Competing leadership instincts coexist without clear dominance.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Tiger vs Monkey = 10%: Impulsive dominance clashes with adaptive manipulation, causing breakdown.`,\n        \"Cat\": `# The Cat\nThe fourth sign: cats are observant, analytical, and psychologically sharp. As the fourth sign they slow the pace, assess risk, and apply intellectual and emotional control to complex situations.\n\nSmart and intellectual: Absorbs complex information rapidly and applies it strategically. Excels in environments requiring analysis, foresight, and psychological awareness.\n\nObservant: Notices subtle behavior shifts and unspoken motive. Uses awareness to navigate situations without direct confrontation or exposure.\n\nQuick reflexes: Responds immediately to sudden changes and maintains control through rapid mental and physical adjustments.\n\nConsiderate: Naturally empathetic and emotionally perceptive. Offers support while maintaining internal emotional boundaries.\n\nIndependent: Prefers full control over environment and decisions. Self-reliance enables high performance but limits collaboration.\n\nGifted in psychology and mind games: Reads human behavior accurately and tests motives through subtle interaction.\n\nSelfish tendencies: Prioritizes personal comfort, autonomy, and goals. Independence is preserved even when group interests are present.\n\nLazy - work smarter not harder: Prioritizes efficiency and leverage over constant effort. Performance peaks when systems reduce required energy.\n\n## Strengths\n- Highly intelligent\n- Deeply observant\n- Emotionally graceful\n- Empathic\n- Strongly independent\n\n## Challenges\n- Secretive\n- Self-prioritizing\n- Energy conserving\n- Too controlling\n- Poor collaborator\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Cat vs Cat = 100%: Shared psychological awareness and caution allow mutual understanding without exposure.\n- Cat vs Goat = 80%: Cat reads intent while goat builds harmony, creating smooth cooperation.\n- Cat vs Pig = 80%: Mental agility and social ease align on quiet strategy with material gain.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Cat vs Tiger = 70%: Cat manages risk through observation while tiger supplies momentum.\n- Cat vs Dog = 70%: Cat assesses quietly while dog protects loyally, forming guarded but stable trust.\n- Cat vs Dragon = 70%: Cat navigates power dynamics carefully while dragon leads openly.\n- Cat vs Rat = 50%: Both operate strategically but hidden manipulation reduces trust.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Cat vs Rooster = 10%: Psychological subtlety clashes with aggressive enforcement, causing breakdown.`,\n        \"Dragon\": `# The Dragon\nThe 5th sign: Dragons embody authority, ambition, and commanding presence. As the fifth sign, they lead visibly, impose direction, and drive large-scale momentum through strength and confidence.\n\nStrong: Possesses high physical and mental endurance. Handles pressure through force and persistence.\n\nConfident: Moves with strong internal certainty. Sets direction simply by acting first.\n\nDirect: Communicates plainly and without hesitation. Values clarity over diplomacy.\n\nLoyal: Commits deeply to chosen people and causes. Loyalty is expressed through protection, consistency, and long-term support.\n\nBossy: Asserts authority directly and forcefully when leading.\n\nMeans What It Says: Aligns words with actions consistently. Trust is built through follow-through.\n\n## Strengths\n- Commanding Presence\n- Unshakable Confidence\n- Deep Loyalty\n- Magnetic Charisma\n- High Resilience\n\n## Challenges\n- Overbearing\n- Blunt to the Point of Friction\n- Chronically Overextended\n- Controlling\n- Inflexible\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Dragon vs Monkey = 100%: Dragon provides authority and direction while Monkey optimizes and adapts systems.\n- Dragon vs Snake = 80%: Power and intuition align, allowing strategy to be enforced with insight.\n- Dragon vs Dragon = 80%: Shared dominance and endurance create strong momentum.\n- Dragon vs Rat = 80%: Strategic intelligence supports Dragon's authority without direct challenge.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Dragon vs Cat = 70%: Cat navigates Dragon's power carefully, avoiding confrontation.\n- Dragon vs Horse = 60%: Force and independence coexist, but coordination is limited.\n- Dragon vs Goat = 50%: Force conflicts with avoidance, reducing reliability under pressure.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Dragon vs Dog = 10%: Dominance clashes with emotional loyalty, creating mistrust and confrontation.`,\n        \"Snake\": `# The Snake\nThe 6th sign. Snakes are intuitive, strategic, and insight-driven. As the sixth sign, they refine power through calculation, preferring subtle control over direct confrontation.\n\nWise: Sees underlying patterns and long-term consequences others miss. Operates through insight, patience, and timing rather than speed or force.\n\nStrategic & Calculating: Plans several steps ahead and weighs long-term consequences. Acts selectively, conserving energy until conditions favor success.\n\nVengeful: Remembers offenses and tracks perceived betrayals.\n\nCharming & Mysterious: Draws others in through knowledge, restraint, and controlled expression.\n\nMaster of Others' Energies: Accurately reads emotional and behavioral states of others.\n\nEither at the Top or Bottom: Operates in extremes rather than moderation.\n\nLoyal: Commits deeply to chosen people while resisting control.\n\n## Strengths\n- Wise\n- Strategic & Calculating\n- Charming & Mysterious\n- Master of Others' Energies\n- Loyal\n\n## Challenges\n- Vengeful\n- Emotionally Closed Off\n- Comfort-Seeking\n- Controlling\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Snake vs Rooster = 100%: Intuition and enforcement align, allowing precise control guided by perception.\n- Snake vs Snake = 80%: Shared intuition and guarded strategy create strong alignment.\n- Snake vs Dragon = 80%: Insight supports power, allowing strategy to be executed with authority.\n- Snake vs Ox = 80%: Stability grounds intuition, enabling steady and strategic progress.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Snake vs Dog = 70%: Loyalty and intuition align once trust is proven.\n- Snake vs Cat = 70%: Mutual perception creates alignment, though trust is carefully tested.\n- Snake vs Rat = 70%: Strategy and intuition combine.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Snake vs Pig = 10%: Guarded control clashes with pleasure seeking, causing withdrawal and mistrust.`,\n        \"Horse\": `# The Horse\nThe 7th sign: Horses are energetic, independent, and work-driven. As the seventh sign, they sustain progress through endurance, autonomy, and relentless forward motion.\n\nHard-working: Sustains high output over extended periods. Relies on effort, repetition, and endurance to achieve results.\n\nStubborn: Resists changing course once momentum is established.\n\nEnergetic & Athletic: Thrives on movement, activity, and stimulation.\n\nImpatient: Goal-driven and easily frustrated by delays.\n\nCharismatic: Naturally attracts attention and social interest.\n\nRebellious: Resists authority and imposed structure.\n\nLoyal: Commits deeply to people and responsibilities once bonded.\n\n## Strengths\n- Athletic\n- Tireless Worker\n- Socially Charismatic\n- Physically Resilient\n- Team-Effective Contributor\n\n## Challenges\n- Stubborn\n- Easily Frustrated by Delays\n- Rebellious Against Authority\n- Overworked\n- Resistant to Adjustment\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Horse vs Dog = 100%: Shared endurance and action-based trust build strong loyalty through effort.\n- Horse vs Goat = 100%: Horse provides drive while Goat smooths alliances, sustaining momentum.\n- Horse vs Tiger = 80%: Momentum and intensity align.\n- Horse vs Horse = 80%: Shared stamina and independence drive results.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Horse vs Snake = 70%: Independence and intuition coexist.\n- Horse vs Cat = 60%: Action and observation coexist, but coordination is limited.\n- Horse vs Dragon = 60%: Force and endurance coexist.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Horse vs Rat = 10%: Independent action clashes with covert manipulation.`,\n        \"Goat\": `# The Goat\nThe 8th sign: Goats are graceful, emotionally intelligent, and socially influential. As the eighth sign, they attract resources and support through charm, harmony, and relational awareness.\n\nMoney-Oriented: Naturally attracts resources through relationships, aesthetics, and emotional intelligence.\n\nPeace-Seeking: Avoids open conflict and prefers subtle influence.\n\nSoft & Delicate: Emotionally sensitive to pressure and tone. This sensitivity enables empathy and connection.\n\nGentle Mannered: Compassionate and nurturing toward others.\n\nMaterialistic: Motivated by financial security, comfort, and tangible rewards.\n\nFeminine Energy: Projects calm, nurturing presence that lowers tension.\n\nManipulative: Influences outcomes subtly through emotional or social leverage.\n\n## Strengths\n- Emotionally Intelligent\n- Gentle in Approach\n- Naturally Graceful\n- Socially Attractive\n- Harmony-Focused\n\n## Challenges\n- Materialistic\n- Subtly Manipulative\n- Emotionally Sensitive\n- Dependency-Prone\n- Stress Reactive\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Goat vs Pig = 100%: Shared pleasure-based wealth building and social harmony create effortless cooperation.\n- Goat vs Horse = 100%: Horse supplies drive while Goat smooths alliances.\n- Goat vs Goat = 80%: Shared values and cooperative instincts create harmony.\n- Goat vs Cat = 80%: Cat handles strategy while Goat maintains harmony.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Goat vs Snake = 70%: Intuition and alliance building align.\n- Goat vs Dragon = 50%: Forceful leadership conflicts with avoidance under pressure.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Goat vs Ox = 10%: Rigid stability suppresses flexibility, causing breakdown in cooperation.`,\n        \"Monkey\": `# The Monkey\nThe 9th sign: Monkeys are clever, adaptive, and mentally agile. As the ninth sign, they optimize systems, solve problems creatively, and upgrade what already exists.\n\nHighly Intelligent: Learns faster than most and adapts instantly to new systems.\n\nQuick-Witted: Responds rapidly to changing conditions.\n\nPlayful: Approaches life through curiosity and experimentation.\n\nCurious: Driven by exploration and learning.\n\nAdaptable: Adjusts smoothly to new environments and changing conditions.\n\nSystem Solvers: Navigates complex environments with logic and creativity.\n\nBeautiful Minds: Displays mental flexibility and rapid perspective-shifting.\n\n## Strengths\n- Highly Intelligent\n- Exceptionally Quick-Witted\n- Adaptable Under Pressure\n- Playful Thinker\n- Deeply Curious\n\n## Challenges\n- Manipulative\n- High Stress / Anxiety\n- Avoids Leadership / Responsibility\n- Bullying Tendencies\n- Easily Distracted\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Monkey vs Dragon = 100%: Dragon provides structure and authority while Monkey optimizes systems.\n- Monkey vs Monkey = 80%: Shared adaptability and learning speed create progress.\n- Monkey vs Rat = 80%: Strategic intelligence aligns.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Monkey vs Horse = 60%: Movement and experimentation coexist.\n- Monkey vs Snake = 60%: Pattern recognition aligns, but trust remains cautious.\n- Monkey vs Cat = 60%: Experimentation and observation coexist.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Monkey vs Tiger = 10%: Impulsive freedom clashes with dominance and intensity, causing breakdown.`,\n        \"Rooster\": `# The Rooster\nThe 10th sign: Roosters are disciplined, confrontational, and precision-driven. As the tenth sign, they enforce structure, protect order, and act decisively when standards are challenged.\n\nConfident & Proud: Carries strong self-belief and visible authority.\n\nLoyal: Stands firmly by people, rules, or principles once committed.\n\nFighter: Confronts challenges directly and persists under resistance.\n\nDetail-Oriented: Focuses intensely on precision and correctness.\n\nCritical & Opinionated: Maintains strong standards and vocal judgments.\n\nLeader: Naturally assumes authority and directs group movement.\n\nObsessive: Fixates on tasks, details, or goals.\n\nAttractive: Commands attention through presence and physical confidence.\n\n## Strengths\n- Confident\n- Strongly Loyal\n- Precision-Focused\n- Visibly Attractive\n- Natural Authority Figure\n\n## Challenges\n- Arrogant\n- Obsessive About Control or Detail\n- Highly Judgmental\n- Self-Promoting\n- Confrontational\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Rooster vs Snake = 100%: Intuition and enforcement align, allowing precise control.\n- Rooster vs Rooster = 80%: Shared discipline and standards create reliability.\n- Rooster vs Ox = 80%: Reliability and enforcement align.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Rooster vs Dragon = 60%: Authority and enforcement overlap.\n- Rooster vs Dog = 60%: Vigilance overlaps, but control instincts create friction.\n- Rooster vs Horse = 60%: Independence and enforcement overlap.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Rooster vs Cat = 10%: Psychological subtlety clashes with aggressive enforcement, causing direct breakdown.`,\n        \"Dog\": `# The Dog\nThe 11th sign: Dogs are loyal, emotionally driven, and justice-oriented. As the eleventh sign, they protect people and principles, forming strong bonds through trust and shared values.\n\nLoyal & Trustworthy: Forms deep bonds and defends people or causes once committed.\n\nHighly Emotional: Experiences emotions deeply and acts from feeling rather than detachment.\n\nHonest & Justice-Oriented: Acts from moral alignment and fairness.\n\nProtective: Actively guards people and values once bonded.\n\nGood Memory: Retains detailed information accurately over long periods.\n\nPossessive: Forms deep attachments that can become controlling.\n\n## Strengths\n- Deeply Loyal and Trustworthy\n- Morally Grounded\n- Protective by Nature\n- Highly Empathetic\n- Exceptional Memory and Investigative Skill\n\n## Challenges\n- Addiction Issues\n- Possessive\n- Emotionally Intense\n- Can become Overbearing\n- Stress-Reactive\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Dog vs Horse = 100%: Trust forms through shared action and endurance.\n- Dog vs Tiger = 80%: Tiger supplies momentum while Dog commits once loyalty is proven.\n- Dog vs Dog = 80%: Shared loyalty and memory create reliability.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Dog vs Cat = 70%: Quiet assessment and loyalty align once trust is tested.\n- Dog vs Snake = 70%: Loyalty and intuition align when trust is proven.\n- Dog vs Pig = 60%: Emotional warmth and loyalty align.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Dog vs Dragon = 10%: Dominance conflicts with emotional loyalty, causing mistrust and confrontation.`,\n        \"Pig\": `# The Pig\nThe 12th sign: Pigs are generous, pleasure-oriented, and community-focused. As the final sign, they close cycles through enjoyment, abundance, and shared experiences.\n\nGood-Natured: Maintains an open, friendly disposition that disarms tension.\n\nLife of the Party: Naturally attracts attention through warmth and ease.\n\nPeople Pleaser: Seeks social approval through generosity and warmth.\n\nPopular: Easily liked and socially accepted.\n\nLucky: Easily encounters success through timing and social networks.\n\nSimple: Prefers ease, comfort, and low complexity.\n\nGenerous: Willingly shares resources and support with others.\n\n## Strengths\n- Good-Natured\n- Generous by Default\n- Social Energizer\n- Widely Liked\n- Strong Collaborator\n\n## Challenges\n- Lazy Under Comfort\n- People-Pleasing\n- Overindulgent\n- Shortcut-Seeking\n- Prone to Weight Gain\n\n## Friendly Signs\n- Pig vs Dog = 100%: Pleasure-based trust and loyalty align.\n- Pig vs Goat = 100%: Shared harmony and alliance-driven wealth building create smooth cooperation.\n- Pig vs Pig = 80%: Shared enjoyment and abundance orientation create ease.\n- Pig vs Cat = 80%: Social warmth and quiet strategy align.\n- Pig vs Tiger = 80%: Momentum and enjoyment coexist.\n\n## Neutral Signs\n- Pig vs Dragon = 60%: Power and pleasure align situationally.\n- Pig vs Horse = 60%: Movement and enjoyment coexist.\n- Pig vs Rat = 60%: Strategy and enjoyment coexist.\n\n## Enemy Signs\n- Pig vs Snake = 10%: Pleasure seeking clashes with guarded control, producing mistrust and withdrawal.`\n    },\n    western: {\n        \"Aries\": `# Aries\nAries is the leader of the zodiac. This sign is assertive, driven, and highly ambitious, operating best when in charge rather than following direction. Aries prefers giving orders over taking them and wants results fast. Action comes before hesitation. This is a spontaneous, hot-headed energy that often moves without fully thinking through consequences. Change, movement, and frequent travel suit Aries well.\n\n## Strengths\n- Aries carries strong business-minded energy and performs well in the material world.\n- Discipline, work ethic, and a competitive drive fuel success.\n- Aries thrives on rivalry, challenges, and the desire to win.\n- A hunger for new experiences and leadership positions naturally places Aries in roles of authority and influence.\n\n## Weaknesses\nImpatience is the primary weakness for Aries. Wanting immediate results often leads to rushed decisions. Acting too quickly can mean choosing the first option instead of the best one. Learning to slow down, weigh options, and wait for the right timing improves outcomes.\n\n## Relationships\nAries brings spontaneity, intensity, and excitement into relationships. Routine and repetition drain interest quickly. Keeping relationships active, varied, and spontaneous is critical. Aries needs frequent change and shared experiences to stay engaged.\n\n## Career & Money\nAries is highly capable in business and money-related fields. Leadership roles suit this sign best - as a founder, manager, executive, or independent operator.\n\n## Health\nAries is associated with the head, brain, and face. Headaches and migraines tend to be more common when stress or intensity is unmanaged.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nLeo and Sagittarius. These signs match Aries ambition, drive, and pace.\n\n### Opposite sign\nLibra. Libra is Aries' opposite and creates friction around balance, timing, and decision making.\n\n## Power Windows\nLeo and Sagittarius seasons are the strongest periods for Aries. During Libra season (September 23 to October 22), Aries benefits from avoiding major risks or impulsive decisions.\n\n## One-line insight\nAries succeeds through decisive action, but lasting results come from pairing speed with timing.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Aries vs Leo = 100%: Shared confidence and leadership create mutual respect and forward momentum.\n- Aries vs Sagittarius = 100%: Independence and action-driven growth align without restriction.\n- Aries vs Gemini = 80%: Speed and curiosity combine, keeping energy high.\n- Aries vs Aquarius = 80%: Action and innovation align, allowing progress without emotional drag.\n- Aries vs Aries = 80%: Shared drive and initiative create momentum, but ego control is required.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Aries vs Pisces = 60%: Drive and sensitivity coexist, though emotional timing differs.\n- Aries vs Taurus = 60%: Speed and stability clash, but cooperation is possible with patience.\n- Aries vs Cancer = 60%: Direct action and emotional caution coexist without alignment.\n- Aries vs Scorpio = 60%: Intensity overlaps, but control dynamics remain unresolved.\n- Aries vs Capricorn = 60%: Impulse and discipline coexist, but authority conflicts slow execution.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Aries vs Libra = 10%: Direct dominance clashes with relational balance, creating constant opposition.`,\n        \"Taurus\": `# Taurus\nTaurus is the wealth sign of the zodiac, often referred to as the banker. This sign is methodical, patient, and highly resistant to change. Taurus prefers routine, structure, and systems that feel reliable and proven. Comfort, stability, and quality matter deeply. Taurus enjoys the finer things in life and works hard to earn them.\n\n## Strengths\n- Taurus has a strong ability to read body language and detect dishonesty instinctively.\n- Patience, persistence, and discipline support long-term success.\n- Taurus excels at building wealth slowly and securely.\n\n## Weaknesses\nStubbornness is Taurus' primary limitation. Once an opinion is formed, it is difficult to change. An overly cautious approach to risk can cause missed opportunities.\n\n## Relationships\nTaurus is deeply loyal but highly possessive in relationships. Absolute trust and loyalty are non-negotiable. Romance is essential, including effort, affection, and intentional gestures.\n\n## Career & Money\nTaurus seeks positions of power, responsibility, and influence. Careers involving money, finance, banking, insurance, property management, and government align naturally.\n\n## Health\nTaurus is associated with the neck, throat, and ears. Sore throats, tension, and colds tend to be more common.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nVirgo and Capricorn. These signs align with Taurus values around stability, structure, and long-term planning.\n\n### Opposite sign\nLeo. Leo energy clashes with Taurus values around security, control, and stability.\n\n## Power Windows\nVirgo and Capricorn seasons are the strongest periods for Taurus. During Leo season (July 23 to August 22), Taurus benefits from avoiding major risks or disruptive changes.\n\n## One Line Insight\nTaurus builds lasting success by prioritizing stability over speed.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Taurus vs Capricorn = 100%: Shared discipline and long-term security focus create steady execution and trust.\n- Taurus vs Virgo = 100%: Practical thinking and patience align.\n- Taurus vs Taurus = 80%: Shared values around stability and comfort create reliability.\n- Taurus vs Pisces = 80%: Emotional sensitivity and material stability complement each other.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Taurus vs Aries = 60%: Speed and stability coexist, but pacing differences limit alignment.\n- Taurus vs Gemini = 60%: Consistency and curiosity coexist, but distraction disrupts.\n- Taurus vs Cancer = 60%: Security and emotional care coexist.\n- Taurus vs Leo = 60%: Comfort and confidence coexist.\n- Taurus vs Libra = 60%: Stability and harmony coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Taurus vs Scorpio = 10%: Control and possession clash, creating power struggle and mistrust.`,\n        \"Gemini\": `# Gemini\nGemini is the sign of communication. This sign thrives on interaction, conversation, and mental stimulation. Gemini needs outlets to express ideas, opinions, and creativity, whether through speaking, writing, sales, media, or social platforms. The Gemini mind moves quickly and becomes bored easily.\n\n## Strengths\n- Gemini is a natural conversationalist and performer.\n- Communication comes easily, whether through speaking, storytelling, sales, or media.\n- Mental agility allows Gemini to juggle multiple ideas at once.\n- Being around a Gemini often feels lively and stimulating.\n\n## Weaknesses\nGemini is prone to mental overload and restlessness. A constantly active mind can lead to anxiety, mood instability, or emotional burnout. Difficulty finishing projects is common when attention is split across too many interests.\n\n## Relationships\nGemini carries a dual nature and can shift moods, interests, and emotional expression quickly. Gemini values humor, stimulation, and conversation more than emotional heaviness.\n\n## Career & Money\nGemini succeeds through communication-based careers. Sales, teaching, speaking, writing, media, marketing, and client-facing roles are strong fits.\n\n## Health\nGemini is associated with the lungs, shoulders, arms, and hands. Anxiety, sleep issues, and mental exhaustion can arise when stimulation is excessive.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nAquarius and Libra. These signs match Gemini intellectually and socially.\n\n### Opposite sign\nSagittarius. Sagittarius creates tension around focus, consistency, and commitment.\n\n## Power Windows\nAquarius and Libra seasons are the strongest periods for Gemini. During Sagittarius period, Gemini benefits from avoiding impulsive commitments.\n\n## One-line insight\nGemini succeeds by mastering communication while learning to finish what it starts.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Gemini vs Aquarius = 100%: Shared intellectual speed and independence create effortless exchange.\n- Gemini vs Libra = 100%: Communication and social intelligence align.\n- Gemini vs Gemini = 80%: Shared curiosity and adaptability keep momentum high.\n- Gemini vs Leo = 80%: Expression and visibility align.\n- Gemini vs Aries = 80%: Speed and initiative combine.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Gemini vs Cancer = 60%: Communication and emotional security coexist.\n- Gemini vs Scorpio = 60%: Curiosity and intensity coexist, but trust develops slowly.\n- Gemini vs Taurus = 60%: Movement and stability coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Gemini vs Sagittarius = 10%: Scattered communication clashes with blunt expansion, causing misunderstanding.`,\n        \"Cancer\": `# Cancer\nCancer is the most emotional sign of the zodiac and experiences life through feeling rather than logic. Love, home, and family are central themes. Cancer needs emotional security and a stable environment to function at its best. Cancer is the nurturer of the zodiac and feels fulfilled when caring for others.\n\nCancer is ruled by the Moon, making this sign highly sensitive to lunar cycles. Emotional intensity increases during full moons.\n\n## Strengths\n- Cancer has strong intuition and emotional awareness.\n- Loyalty is one of Cancer's strongest traits, with a ride-or-die mindset toward loved ones.\n- Cancer provides stability, care, and emotional support.\n\n## Weaknesses\nDeep emotional sensitivity leads to overattachment, stress, and difficulty letting go. Cancer may worry excessively about things outside of their control. Holding on to the past or to unhealthy connections can prevent growth.\n\n## Relationships\nCancer is deeply relationship-oriented and does best in committed, emotionally secure partnerships. Love is the primary priority. Cancer nurtures partners through affection, care, and consistency.\n\n## Career & Money\nTrust between colleagues and business partners is important. Cancer struggles in environments where loyalty is uncertain.\n\n## Health\nCancer is associated with the chest, stomach, and digestive system. Emotional stress often manifests physically.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nPisces and Scorpio. These signs align emotionally and intuitively with Cancer.\n\n### Opposite sign\nCapricorn. Capricorn energy creates tension around emotional expression, priorities, and control.\n\n## Power Windows\nPisces and Scorpio seasons are the strongest periods for Cancer. During Capricorn season (December 22 to January 19), Cancer benefits from avoiding major risks.\n\n## One Line Insight\nCancer thrives by building emotional security while learning when to let go.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Cancer vs Scorpio = 100%: Emotional loyalty and depth reinforce each other.\n- Cancer vs Cancer = 80%: Shared emotional awareness and need for security create stability.\n- Cancer vs Virgo = 80%: Practical care and emotional sensitivity coexist.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Cancer vs Sagittarius = 60%: Security and freedom coexist, but long-term direction diverges.\n- Cancer vs Aries = 60%: Emotional caution and direct action coexist without alignment.\n- Cancer vs Gemini = 60%: Emotional depth and communication coexist.\n- Cancer vs Taurus = 60%: Security and stability coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Cancer vs Capricorn = 10%: Emotional nurturing clashes with rigid authority and control, breaking trust.`,\n        \"Leo\": `# Leo\nLeo is driven by fun, excitement, and self-expression. This sign thrives on movement, entertainment, and variety and struggles when life becomes repetitive or stagnant. Leo needs stimulation, adventure, and social engagement to stay energized. Being seen, admired, and appreciated plays a major role in confidence and performance.\n\n## Strengths\n- Leo carries natural charisma and presence.\n- Others look to Leo for leadership, direction, and confidence.\n- This sign operates well in the spotlight and commands attention through personality and force of presence.\n- Leo thrives when respected and performs strongly in roles that require authority, confidence, and visibility.\n\n## Weaknesses\nLeo may make impulsive or emotional decisions, particularly around spending and commitments. When bored or under-stimulated, Leo may act recklessly or seek validation in unhealthy ways.\n\n## Relationships\nLeo seeks excitement, adventure, and constant engagement in relationships. Routine and quiet domestic life drain interest. Maintaining novelty, affection, and mutual admiration is key to long-term stability.\n\n## Career & Money\nLeo performs best in leadership and authority-driven roles. Being the boss, decision maker, or public-facing leader aligns naturally.\n\n## Health\nLeo is associated with the heart, back, spine, and blood. Back tension and strain are common, especially when stress is unmanaged.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nAries and Sagittarius. These signs match Leo energy, enthusiasm, and pace.\n\n### Opposite sign\nAquarius. Aquarius energy clashes with Leo around attention, values, and direction.\n\n## Power Windows\nAries and Sagittarius seasons are the strongest periods for Leo. During Aquarius season (January 21 to February 18), Leo benefits from avoiding impulsive decisions.\n\n## One-line insight\nLeo performs best when confidence is balanced with restraint.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Leo vs Sagittarius = 100%: Confidence and adventure align.\n- Leo vs Aries = 100%: Shared leadership and drive create mutual respect.\n- Leo vs Leo = 80%: Shared confidence and presence align, though ego balance is required.\n- Leo vs Gemini = 80%: Expression and communication combine.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Leo vs Capricorn = 60%: Confidence and discipline coexist.\n- Leo vs Scorpio = 60%: Pride and intensity overlap.\n- Leo vs Cancer = 60%: Visibility and emotional security coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Leo vs Aquarius = 10%: Attention-seeking leadership clashes with detachment and independence.`,\n        \"Virgo\": `# Virgo\nVirgo is the perfectionist of the zodiac. This sign is detail-oriented, methodical, and focused on doing things the right way. Virgo pays close attention to systems, order, and efficiency and feels most stable when life is structured and controlled. Being productive and useful is essential.\n\n## Strengths\n- Virgo has exceptional attention to detail and a strong ability to identify flaws, inefficiencies, and inconsistencies.\n- Discipline, reliability, and high standards allow Virgo to produce consistent results.\n- When focused, Virgo's precision becomes a major advantage.\n\n## Weaknesses\nPerfectionism can become a limitation. Overanalyzing small details may slow progress or create unnecessary stress. Virgo may judge others too harshly and apply the same criticism inward, leading to self-doubt.\n\n## Relationships\nVirgo holds high standards in relationships and may prefer being alone over settling for less than expected. Long-term success improves when Virgo maintains standards while allowing flexibility.\n\n## Career & Money\nVirgo excels in careers that reward precision, analysis, and problem detection. Roles involving investigation, quality control, organization, research, auditing, or system improvement align well.\n\n## Health\nVirgo is associated with the abdomen, intestines, and digestive system. Mental stress often shows up physically.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nTaurus and Capricorn. These signs align with Virgo's need for stability, structure, and long-term planning.\n\n### Opposite sign\nPisces. Pisces energy clashes with Virgo around order, boundaries, and practicality.\n\n## Power Windows\nTaurus and Capricorn seasons are the strongest periods for Virgo. During Pisces season, Virgo benefits from avoiding major risks or emotionally driven commitments.\n\n## One-line insight\nVirgo succeeds by applying high standards without becoming trapped by perfection.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Virgo vs Capricorn = 100%: Shared discipline and long-term planning create stable execution.\n- Virgo vs Taurus = 100%: Practical thinking and patience align.\n- Virgo vs Virgo = 80%: Shared precision and discipline align.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Virgo vs Libra = 60%: Logic and balance coexist.\n- Virgo vs Scorpio = 60%: Precision and intensity overlap.\n- Virgo vs Cancer = 60%: Practical care and emotional nurturing coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Virgo vs Pisces = 10%: Practical realism clashes with emotional idealism, breaking trust and execution.`,\n        \"Libra\": `# Libra\nLibra seeks balance, harmony, and control over their environment. Sudden changes, chaos, or uncertainty disrupt their inner stability. Represented by the scales, Libra has a strong internal sense of justice and constantly evaluates whether situations and people are balanced, fair, and justified. This sign is highly karmic - actions carry immediate consequences.\n\n## Strengths\n- Libra has a strong moral compass and an exceptional ability to detect dishonesty.\n- This sign is highly diplomatic and skilled at mediation, problem-solving, and maintaining peace.\n- Libra is strongly connected to beauty, aesthetics, and refinement.\n\n## Weaknesses\nIndecision and emotional inconsistency are Libra's primary challenges. Shifts in mood or perspective can happen quickly, confusing others and disrupting long-term plans. Confidence is closely tied to appearance and environment.\n\n## Relationships\nLibra thrives on admiration and attention in relationships. Feeling desired and valued is essential. Clear communication is critical, as unspoken expectations often lead to misunderstandings.\n\n## Career & Money\nLibra performs best in roles that involve visibility, admiration, or judgment. Acting, modeling, influencing, media, and public-facing careers align well. Libra also excels in law, mediation, or any role requiring truth detection.\n\n## Health\nLibra is associated with the kidneys, adrenal glands, and skin. Hydration and balance are important.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nAquarius and Gemini. These signs support Libra mentally, socially, and creatively.\n\n### Opposite sign\nAries. Aries energy clashes with Libra around pace, decision-making, and emotional balance.\n\n## Power Windows\nAquarius and Gemini seasons are the strongest periods for Libra. During Aries season (March 21 to April 20), Libra benefits from avoiding rushed decisions.\n\n## One Line Insight\nLibra succeeds by maintaining balance without avoiding decisive action.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Libra vs Gemini = 100%: Communication and social intelligence align.\n- Libra vs Aquarius = 100%: Shared ideals and intellectual balance allow cooperation.\n- Libra vs Sagittarius = 100%: Freedom and harmony align through shared values.\n- Libra vs Libra = 80%: Shared balance-seeking and diplomacy create smooth interaction.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Libra vs Taurus = 60%: Stability and harmony coexist.\n- Libra vs Cancer = 60%: Emotional sensitivity and balance coexist.\n- Libra vs Scorpio = 60%: Balance and intensity coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Libra vs Aries = 10%: Balance-seeking clashes with direct dominance, creating constant opposition.`,\n        \"Scorpio\": `# Scorpio\nScorpio is the most private and intense sign of the zodiac. This sign moves in silence, revealing little about plans, intentions, or inner thoughts. Scorpio values secrecy, mystery, and control over information. Power comes from observation rather than explanation. Scorpio prefers action over words and allows results to speak. There is a strong attraction to the unknown, the hidden, anything operating beneath the surface. Emotional intensity runs deep and when provoked, Scorpio can become vengeful. Trust is everything and betrayal is rarely forgiven.\n\n## Strengths\n- Scorpio has a natural ability to read people instantly, particularly through eye contact.\n- Hidden intentions, dishonesty, and unspoken motives are often detected without effort.\n- Focus, emotional depth, and resilience allow Scorpio to handle extreme situations that overwhelm others.\n\n## Weaknesses\nScorpio is strongly associated with revenge and jealousy. When wronged there is a tendency to seek immediate retribution. Scorpio often lives a karmic life where actions quickly cycle back, making impulsive reactions risky.\n\n## Relationships\nScorpio is the most dominant sign in relationships. Loyalty is expected without question and emotional or physical betrayal is intolerable. Scorpio is deeply possessive and requires full commitment from a partner.\n\n## Career\nScorpio excels in careers that involve uncovering truth and understanding human behavior - psychology, therapy, interrogation, investigation, research, data analysis, and intelligence-based roles.\n\n## Health\nScorpio is associated with bladder, reproductive organs, and sexual health. Emotional regulation plays a significant role in overall well-being.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nPisces and Cancer. These signs align emotionally and intuitively with Scorpio.\n\n### Opposite sign\nTaurus. Taurus energy clashes with Scorpio around control, attachment, and values.\n\n## Power Windows\nPisces and Cancer seasons are the strongest periods for Scorpio. During Taurus season (April 20 to May 20), Scorpio benefits from avoiding major risks or emotionally charged confrontations.\n\n## One-line insight\nScorpio gains power by observing longer than acting.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Scorpio vs Capricorn = 100%: Shared ambition and discipline align, allowing power to be built steadily.\n- Scorpio vs Pisces = 100%: Emotional depth and intuition align, creating strong psychological trust.\n- Scorpio vs Cancer = 100%: Emotional loyalty and protection reinforce each other.\n- Scorpio vs Scorpio = 80%: Shared intensity and focus create strong alignment.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Scorpio vs Aquarius = 60%: Intensity and detachment co-exist.\n- Scorpio vs Sagittarius = 60%: Depth and freedom co-exist.\n- Scorpio vs Aries = 60%: Power and pulse co-exist.\n- Scorpio vs Gemini = 60%: Depth and curiosity co-exist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Scorpio vs Taurus = 10%: Control and possession clash, creating power struggle and mistrust.`,\n        \"Sagittarius\": `# Sagittarius\nSagittarius is the most open-minded sign of the zodiac. This sign is driven by freedom, exploration, and constant movement. Sagittarius needs change, travel, and new environments to stay mentally and emotionally healthy. Sagittarius is naturally drawn to foreign cultures, different belief systems, and life experiences outside familiar territory. Independence is non-negotiable.\n\n## Strengths\n- Sagittarius is direct, honest, and improvement-focused.\n- This sign does not sugarcoat opinions and speaks openly about what can be done better.\n- Open-mindedness and curiosity support learning, adaptation, and growth.\n- Sagittarius naturally pushes others to aim higher and move faster.\n\n## Weaknesses\nIndecision and inconsistency can undermine long-term stability. Sagittarius may change direction suddenly, particularly in relationships or commitments. A strong all-or-nothing mindset can lead to abandoning situations that no longer feel ideal.\n\n## Relationships\nSagittarius values honesty, independence, and freedom in relationships. Sagittarius needs spontaneity, movement, and shared experiences with a partner. Feeling controlled or restricted causes interest to fade quickly.\n\n## Career & Money\nSagittarius performs best in careers that involve movement, travel, or constant variation. Traditional desk jobs and repetitive routines are poorly suited.\n\n## Health\nSagittarius is associated with the hips, thighs, sciatic nerves, and liver. Regular movement and time outdoors support both physical and mental health.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nLeo, Aries, and Capricorn. These signs support Sagittarius energy, ambition, and momentum.\n\n### Opposite sign\nGemini. Gemini energy creates tension around focus, consistency, and commitment.\n\n## Power Windows\nLeo, Aries, and Capricorn seasons are the strongest periods for Sagittarius. During Gemini season, Sagittarius benefits from avoiding impulsive commitments.\n\n## One-line insight\nSagittarius thrives by staying in motion while committing to the right direction.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Sagittarius vs Aries = 100%: Shared action orientation and independence create momentum.\n- Sagittarius vs Leo = 100%: Confidence and adventure align.\n- Sagittarius vs Libra = 100%: Freedom and balance align through shared ideals.\n- Sagittarius vs Sagittarius = 80%: Shared optimism and independence fuel growth.\n- Sagittarius vs Aquarius = 80%: Big-picture thinking and freedom align.\n- Sagittarius vs Capricorn = 80%: Expansion pairs with discipline.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Sagittarius vs Cancer = 60%: Freedom and emotional security coexist.\n- Sagittarius vs Scorpio = 60%: Exploration and depth coexist.\n- Sagittarius vs Taurus = 60%: Adventure and routine coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Sagittarius vs Gemini = 10%: Blunt expansion clashes with scattered communication.`,\n        \"Capricorn\": `# Capricorn\nCapricorn is the most business-focused and money-oriented sign of the zodiac. This sign is practical, disciplined, and driven by results. Capricorn evaluates people and situations based on usefulness, reliability, and long-term value. Emotions are secondary to logic. Seriousness, structure, and control define how Capricorn moves through life. Loyalty is strong once trust is earned. Capricorn often matures later than other signs, facing early difficulty but gaining strength, wisdom, and dominance with age.\n\n## Strengths\n- Capricorn has a strong logical mindset and the ability to see reality clearly, even when others avoid it.\n- Discipline, patience, and long-range thinking support leadership and financial success.\n- Capricorn is dependable, trustworthy, and highly capable of carrying responsibility over long periods.\n\n## Weaknesses\nEmotional detachment can create difficulty when dealing with sensitive or highly emotional people. Capricorn may appear cold or overly serious, which can limit connection. Chaos and uncertainty disrupt performance.\n\n## Relationships\nCapricorn is one of the most loyal signs in the zodiac. Commitment is taken seriously and intended to last. Financial responsibility and long-term potential matter greatly.\n\n## Career & Money\nCapricorn is the primary money maker of the zodiac. Leadership roles, executive positions, and authority-driven careers align naturally. Finance-related fields such as banking, insurance, planning, and asset management are strong paths.\n\n## Health\nCapricorn is associated with the bones, knees, and joints. Joint strain and knee discomfort tend to appear over time.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nTaurus, Virgo, and Sagittarius. These signs support Capricorn values around structure, discipline, and progress.\n\n### Opposite sign\nCancer. Cancer energy clashes with Capricorn around emotional expression and priorities.\n\n## Power Windows\nTaurus, Virgo, and Sagittarius seasons are the strongest periods for Capricorn. During Cancer season, Capricorn benefits from avoiding emotionally driven decisions.\n\n## One-line insight\nCapricorn builds lasting power by prioritizing structure, patience, and long-term vision.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Capricorn vs Scorpio = 100%: Shared ambition, discipline, and control align to build power steadily.\n- Capricorn vs Taurus = 100%: Long-term security, patience, and material focus align.\n- Capricorn vs Virgo = 100%: Discipline and precision align, producing reliable execution.\n- Capricorn vs Capricorn = 80%: Shared ambition and discipline create steady momentum.\n- Capricorn vs Aquarius = 80%: Structure and vision align.\n- Capricorn vs Pisces = 80%: Emotional insight softens discipline, creating balance.\n- Capricorn vs Sagittarius = 80%: Expansion and structure combine.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Capricorn vs Aries = 60%: Impulse and discipline coexist.\n- Capricorn vs Gemini = 60%: Strategy and curiosity coexist.\n- Capricorn vs Leo = 60%: Authority and confidence coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Capricorn vs Cancer = 10%: Rigid authority clashes with emotional nurturing, breaking trust and safety.`,\n        \"Aquarius\": `# Aquarius\nAquarius is the trailblazer of the zodiac. This sign is driven by originality, independence, and a refusal to follow established norms. Aquarius prefers to operate outside traditional systems. Rebellion against outdated structures is natural. Aquarius is open-minded and future-oriented, drawn toward new ideas, alternative systems, and higher-level thinking.\n\n## Strengths\nAquarius thrives by doing things differently. Independence, innovation, and unconventional thinking create advantage. Aquarius excels at identifying new opportunities, building alternative business models, and approaching money from non-traditional angles.\n\n## Weaknesses\nBoredom is a primary challenge. Aquarius loses interest quickly when stimulation fades. A short attention span can lead to unfinished projects. Constant novelty is needed to stay engaged.\n\n## Relationships\nAquarius is both a lover and a best friend, which can be difficult to find. Without that balance, commitment becomes unstable. Freedom is the highest value, and any attempt to restrict it leads to withdrawal.\n\n## Career & Money\nMetaphysical systems, alternative data, or new technologies create advantage. International work and global income streams are strongly favored. When everyone moves one way, Aquarius benefits from choosing the opposite route.\n\n## Health\nAquarius is associated with the lower legs, ankles, and circulation. Supporting circulation and maintaining mobility in the lower body improves physical stability.\n\n## One-Line Insight\nAquarius succeeds by breaking patterns while staying disciplined enough to finish what it starts.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Aquarius vs Gemini = 100%: Shared intellectual speed and curiosity create effortless exchange.\n- Aquarius vs Libra = 100%: Balance and vision align, allowing cooperation through ideas.\n- Aquarius vs Aquarius = 80%: Shared independence and vision align.\n- Aquarius vs Aries = 80%: Innovation and action combine.\n- Aquarius vs Capricorn = 80%: Vision pairs with structure.\n- Aquarius vs Sagittarius = 80%: Big-picture thinking and freedom align.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Aquarius vs Pisces = 60%: Vision and sensitivity coexist.\n- Aquarius vs Cancer = 60%: Detachment and emotional bonding coexist.\n- Aquarius vs Taurus = 60%: Innovation and stability coexist.\n- Aquarius vs Virgo = 60%: Vision and analysis coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Aquarius vs Leo = 10%: Detachment clashes with attention-seeking leadership, creating opposition.`,\n        \"Pisces\": `# Pisces\nPisces is the dreamer of the zodiac and is deeply connected to the inner world of imagination and dreams. This sign often receives insight, messages, and clarity through dreams and altered states of awareness. Pisces tends to live partly in the inner world rather than fully grounded in physical reality. Imagination is powerful and constant. Living near water strongly supports emotional balance and intuitive strength.\n\n## Strengths\n- Pisces has a natural ability to see the best in people and imagine who they can become.\n- This makes Pisces highly effective at coaching, guiding, and uplifting others.\n- Creativity, imagination, and empathy allow Pisces to inspire growth and transformation.\n\n## Weaknesses\nEscapism is the primary risk for Pisces. Discomfort with the harshness of reality can lead to avoidance behaviors. Pisces may lose themselves within groups or causes, neglecting personal boundaries.\n\n## Relationships\nPisces often forms relationships based on potential rather than reality. There is a tendency to nurture and elevate a partner. Mutual growth and openness to change are necessary for long-term stability.\n\n## Career & Money\nSales, government positions, advocacy, and any career requiring convincing others align well. Working within a team or collective amplifies effectiveness.\n\n## Health\nNervous system, feet, thalamus, and lymphatic system. Sensitivity can lead to stress-related illness. Emotional well-being is closely tied to physical health.\n\n## Compatibility\n### Friendly signs\nCancer and Scorpio. These signs align emotionally and intuitively with Pisces. Water sign alignment supports trust, creativity, and emotional flow.\n\n### Opposite sign\nVirgo. Virgo energy clashes with Pisces around structure, control, and boundaries.\n\n## Power Windows\nCancer and Scorpio seasons are the strongest periods for Pisces. During Virgo season, Pisces benefits from avoiding major risks or overly rigid environments.\n\n## One Line Insight\nPisces thrives by honoring imagination while staying anchored in reality.\n\n## Aligned Signs\n- Pisces vs Cancer = 100%: Emotional sensitivity and nurturing align, creating deep trust.\n- Pisces vs Scorpio = 100%: Intuition and emotional depth align, forming strong psychological bonding.\n- Pisces vs Capricorn = 80%: Emotional insight pairs with structure.\n- Pisces vs Taurus = 80%: Sensitivity and material security complement each other.\n\n## Dynamic Signs\n- Pisces vs Aquarius = 60%: Vision and sensitivity coexist.\n- Pisces vs Aries = 60%: Drive and emotion coexist.\n- Pisces vs Gemini = 60%: Imagination and curiosity coexist.\n- Pisces vs Leo = 60%: Sensitivity and confidence coexist.\n- Pisces vs Libra = 60%: Compassion and balance coexist.\n- Pisces vs Sagittarius = 60%: Idealism and freedom coexist.\n\n## Oppositional Signs\n- Pisces vs Virgo = 10%: Emotional idealism clashes with rigid realism, breaking trust and flow.`\n    },\n    careers: {\n        1: `# 💼 1 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nLeadership, Decision-making, Independence, Strategic Vision\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n1 lifepaths work best when they are in charge. Being a follower long term is draining because you are built to make decisions, set direction, and take responsibility. You do better when your name is on the results and you have room to move without someone micromanaging you.\n\nCEO, Founder, Manager, Supervisor, Lawyer, Finance, Athlete, Sales Leader\n\n## Work Environment\nYou work best in leadership positions where you can be the one giving orders rather than taking them. You thrive under pressure.\n\n## Challenges\nLearning to take advice from others and avoiding arrogance in high-stakes environments.`,\n        3: `# 💼 3 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nCommunication, Networking, Creativity, Multitasking\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n3 lifepaths need to talk, sell, entertain, and stay in motion. The worst thing for a 3 is doing the same exact thing everyday with no social life built into the job. You do best when you can bounce between projects and keep things fresh.\n\nSales, Marketing, Social Media, PR, Content Creation, Writing, Podcasting, Entertainment\n\n## Work Environment\nA main job plus side hustles is usually the winning formula. You need to keep things fresh and switch between tasks frequently.\n\n## Challenges\nFinishing what you start. Bright ideas come easily but require focus and discipline to reach their full potential.`,\n        4: `# 💼 4 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nOrganization, Reliability, Systematic Thinking, Discipline\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n4 lifepaths are built for structure, systems, and real responsibility. You are the person who shows up early, stays consistent, and outworks everybody. You excel when you can build something that lasts.\n\nGovernment, Security, Accounting, Bookkeeping, Engineering, Operations, Logistics, Construction\n\n## Work Environment\nYou thrive in controlled environments where operations and systems are clear. You outwork others through steady effort and routine.\n\n## Challenges\nGetting stuck doing the hard work without getting the credit. Ensure your effort is rewarded and move on if a system is broken.`,\n        5: `# 💼 5 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nAdaptability, Charisma, Networking, Resourcefulness\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n5 lifepaths need freedom, variety, movement, and new environments. A strict routine job will make you feel trapped. You need work that includes travel, events, people, or constant change.\n\n- Travel industry\n- Hotel business\n- Event planning\n- Modeling\n- Driving\n- Pilot\n- Health industry\n- International business\n\n## Work Environment\nYour goal is to build a career that feels like a lifestyle. Stagnation is your enemy — you need to experience change to stay motivated.\n\n## Challenges\nDecision-making and commitment. You can be indecisive and change your mind at the last moment, which can impact long-term growth.`,\n        6: `# 💼 6 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nNurturing, Responsibility, Teamwork, Problem-solving\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n6 lifepaths work best in roles where you are needed. You do well when you feel like your effort helps people and creates stability. Team culture matters, and you usually do better in friendly environments than cutthroat ones.\n\nReal Estate, Caretaker, Assistant, Government, Food Industry, Education Support, Service-based Careers\n\n## Work Environment\nYou are a natural team player who thrives on collective success. You enjoy working together with others to build something significant.\n\n## Challenges\nSetting boundaries. You may solve everyone else's problems while neglecting your own goals and potential.`,\n        7: `# 💼 7 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nAnalysis, Independent Research, Problem-solving, Deep Thinking\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n7 lifepaths need to work with the mind, not the body. Physical labor drains a 7 over time even if they are strong. You do best alone, or with minimal social demands, and you usually outperform people when you are left to focus.\n\nProgrammer, Analyst, Researcher, IT, Cybersecurity, Teacher, Designer, Data Work, Remote Business\n\n## Work Environment\nTechnology is your cheat code to making money. You want to use your brain and intelligence rather than physical labor.\n\n## Challenges\nCommunication with others who can't keep up with your quick cognitive pace. Patience with slower thinkers is a skill worth building.`,\n        8: `# 💼 8 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nFinancial Acumen, Leadership, Risk Management, Strategy\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n8 lifepaths do best when money is the focus and the environment is serious. You perform better when you are around transactions, assets, business, and power. Money problems can throw you off, so financial stability is not optional.\n\nBanker, Accountant, Insurance, Sales, Business Owner, Finance, Investing, Real Estate\n\n## Work Environment\nYou thrive in high-stakes environments where you can manage power and resources. You are destined for abundance through karmic balance.\n\n## Challenges\nUps and downs with money. You are good at making it but also good at losing it. Aim for long-term growth over short-term boosts.`,\n        9: `# 💼 9 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nAdaptability, Reverse Engineering, Strategic Support, Observation\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n9 lifepaths can succeed in almost anything because you adapt fast, but your environment decides your outcome. You do better behind the scenes, improving systems, supporting leaders, and making things run smoother.\n\nAssistant, Secretary, Operations Support, Coordination, Behind-the-scenes Business, Crypto, Strategy\n\n## Work Environment\nYou pick up qualities from those around you. Being around high performers boosts you while negative settings drag you down.\n\n## Challenges\nEgo and addictive personality. Do not let your self-image grow larger than your purpose or fall into negative habits.`,\n        11: `# 💼 11 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nInspiration, Intuition, Charisma, Vision\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n11 lifepaths need passion or they crash. You will not reach your potential doing work you do not care about. When you believe in something, you outperform everyone, but you also struggle when your boss is weak.\n\nAthlete, Actor, Influencer, Author, Consulting, Coaching, Design, Creative Direction\n\n## Work Environment\nA main job plus side hustles is usually the winning formula. You need to keep things fresh and switch between tasks frequently.\n\n## Challenges\nFinishing what you start. Bright ideas come easily but require focus and discipline to reach their full potential.`,\n        22: `# 💼 22 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nVision, Legacy Building, Strategy, Manifestation\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n22 lifepaths are master builders. You are here to build something real, something that lasts, and you naturally upgrade people and businesses around you. The best path is building your own company, brand, or system.\n\nArchitect, Engineer, Construction, Strategist, Financial Institutions, Personal Trainer, Business Building\n\n## Work Environment\nYou are a master strategist who turns chaos into structure. You are often better at building up others than you are for yourself.\n\n## Challenges\nSpending years building someone else's dream. Be sure the results of your hard work stay with you and your legacy.`,\n        28: `# 💼 28 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nStrategy, Financial Magnetism, Authority, Precision\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n28 lifepaths work best when money, power, or high stakes are involved. You are built for pressure and responsibility and usually perform better when outcomes matter. Passive roles or capped income drain you.\n\nBusiness Owner, Entrepreneur, Finance, Sales, Real Estate, Negotiation, Leadership, High Stakes Work\n\n## Work Environment\nYou move with strategy and build through decisive action. You naturally pull money and opportunity into your orbit through precision.\n\n## Challenges\nWasted time and emotional distance. Your ambition can isolate you if you do not maintain personal balance.`,\n        33: `# 💼 33 Life Path — Careers\n\n## Professional Strengths\nInfluence, Teaching, Visionary Leadership, Trailblazing\n\n## Ideal Career Paths\n33 lifepaths do best when their work impacts people. You are not built to live a small life or just clock in and clock out. When you commit to a mission, your presence elevates everything around you.\n\nTeacher, Planner, Strategist, Visionary, Influencer, Community Leader, Purpose-driven Entrepreneur\n\n## Work Environment\nYou have limitless potential to change the world. Your power is in influence, and wherever you direct your attention, others follow.\n\n## Challenges\nTough challenges and pushback from the masses. Being three steps ahead can leave you feeling misunderstood by those you lead.`\n    },\n    personalYear: {\n        1: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 1\nA year of new beginnings and fresh starts. Plant seeds for long-term projects. Independence, leadership, and initiative are the dominant themes. What you begin now sets the tone for the next 9-year cycle.\n\nFocus on yourself. Make bold moves. Avoid relying too heavily on others — this is the year to trust your own instincts and act on them. The energy favors those who step forward rather than wait.\n\n## Focus On\n- Starting something new\n- Taking the lead in your own life\n- Building confidence and independence\n\n## Avoid\n- Hesitation and second-guessing\n- Over-relying on others for direction\n- Clinging to what the last cycle built`,\n        2: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 2\nA year of patience, partnership, and heightened sensitivity. Focus on relationships, diplomacy, and cooperation. Things move slowly and that is by design — this is a year to refine and connect, not to rush.\n\nCollaboration opens doors that individual effort cannot. Pay attention to the subtle details in your relationships and environment. Emotional sensitivity runs higher this year, so be mindful of how you interpret events.\n\n## Focus On\n- Building and deepening relationships\n- Collaboration and diplomacy\n- Patience and careful attention to detail\n\n## Avoid\n- Forcing decisions or timelines\n- Reacting to situations before they fully develop\n- Neglecting your emotional needs`,\n        3: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 3\nA year of creativity, communication, and social expansion. Express yourself freely and put ideas into the world. Travel, new connections, and creative projects thrive in a 3 year.\n\nThis is a lighter, more joyful energy after the slower rhythm of the 2. Share what you know, connect with new people, and allow yourself to enjoy the process. The risk is scattering energy across too many directions.\n\n## Focus On\n- Creative projects and self-expression\n- Social connections and networking\n- Communication in all forms\n\n## Avoid\n- Overcommitting to too many things at once\n- Neglecting depth in favor of entertainment\n- Ignoring practical responsibilities`,\n        4: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 4\nA year of work, structure, and foundation building. Efforts put in now create lasting results. It is a grounding year — slow, steady, and demanding. Discipline pays off and shortcuts backfire.\n\nDo not expect rapid movement. The 4 year rewards those who show up consistently, lay careful groundwork, and resist the urge to take the easy path. What you build this year is meant to last.\n\n## Focus On\n- Discipline and consistent effort\n- Building systems and structure\n- Long-term investments of time and energy\n\n## Avoid\n- Shortcuts and quick fixes\n- Ignoring health or financial foundations\n- Resistance to hard work`,\n        5: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 5\nA year of change, freedom, and unexpected movement. Life shifts this year and resistance only creates friction. Travel, new people, and new experiences are all strongly favored.\n\nAdaptability is your greatest asset. Plans made in a 5 year often get rerouted — this is not failure, it is course correction. Stay flexible and lean into the unexpected rather than fighting it.\n\n## Focus On\n- Embracing change and new experiences\n- Travel and expansion\n- Flexibility and adaptability\n\n## Avoid\n- Forcing rigid plans or outcomes\n- Holding too tightly to what was\n- Reckless impulsiveness (change does not mean chaos)`,\n        6: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 6\nA year of responsibility, home, and relationships. Family matters come to the forefront and commitments deepen. This is a nurturing year — invest in the people and environments that matter most.\n\nLove, service, and community are the defining themes. Decisions about home, relationships, and long-term commitments made this year carry significant weight. Guard against over-giving at the expense of your own needs.\n\n## Focus On\n- Family, home, and close relationships\n- Service and community\n- Deepening long-term commitments\n\n## Avoid\n- Taking on others' burdens at the cost of your own wellbeing\n- Neglecting yourself while caring for others\n- Avoiding necessary relationship conversations`,\n        7: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 7\nA year of reflection, study, and inner development. Pull back from external noise and invest in knowledge, spiritual growth, and self-understanding. This is not a year for forced external action.\n\nThe 7 year often feels quiet or even isolating — this is intentional. Trust what is developing beneath the surface. Solitude is productive. Research, study, and introspection now build the foundation for significant external movement in the year that follows.\n\n## Focus On\n- Study, research, and self-knowledge\n- Spiritual or philosophical development\n- Rest and inner reflection\n\n## Avoid\n- Forcing external results before they are ready\n- Overextending socially when solitude is calling\n- Ignoring intuition in favor of logic alone`,\n        8: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 8\nA year of power, ambition, and financial movement. Career and money are the primary focus. What you have built over the last 7 years comes up for harvest — take strategic action and pursue opportunities with confidence.\n\nThis is a year of karmic financial balance. What you have invested in ethically comes back multiplied. What has been built on shortcuts or dishonesty may also come to account. Operate with integrity and full commitment.\n\n## Focus On\n- Career advancement and financial strategy\n- Authority and leadership\n- Long-term wealth building\n\n## Avoid\n- Short-term thinking in financial matters\n- Arrogance in positions of power\n- Neglecting relationships for ambition`,\n        9: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 9\nA year of completion, release, and endings. Clear out what no longer serves and prepare for the new cycle that begins in the 1 year. This is not the year to start new long-term commitments — it is the year to close chapters.\n\nForgiveness, letting go, and gratitude are the central themes. Resisting the energy of closure this year creates drag that follows you into the next cycle. Trust the endings. Something better is ready to begin.\n\n## Focus On\n- Completing and closing long-standing projects or relationships\n- Forgiveness and emotional release\n- Gratitude for the full cycle\n\n## Avoid\n- Starting major new long-term ventures\n- Holding onto what has clearly run its course\n- Allowing endings to become sources of bitterness`,\n        11: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 11\nA master number year — 11 is the number of the guide and the visionary. This is a powerful year to start or release something you want to be influential. When 11 energy is channeled well, it creates work and connections that inspire others.\n\nEmotionality is heightened in an 11 year. You may find yourself more sensitive, more reactive, or more tuned in than usual. Be discerning about how you interpret events — not everything that feels significant is. Ground yourself regularly and direct your heightened perception toward creation rather than anxiety.\n\n## Focus On\n- Visionary projects and influential work\n- Intuition and spiritual development\n- Sharing your gifts with a wider audience\n\n## Avoid\n- Getting lost in emotional overwhelm\n- Misreading situations through heightened sensitivity\n- Shrinking from visibility out of fear`,\n        22: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 22\nA master number year — 22 is the number of the master builder. This is a year of large-scale vision and the genuine potential to build something that matters. The work required is intense but what is created can last a generation.\n\nDo not shrink from the scale of what this year is asking of you. The 22 year demands structure, discipline, and courage. It rewards those who think big and execute with precision. This is not a year for small plans.\n\n## Focus On\n- Large-scale building and long-term legacy\n- Disciplined execution of ambitious visions\n- Collaborating with others who match your standard\n\n## Avoid\n- Playing small out of fear of what building big requires\n- Cutting corners on important foundations\n- Allowing perfectionism to prevent action`,\n        33: `# 🗓️ Personal Year 33\nA master number year — 33 is the number of the master teacher. This is a year of service, influence, and purpose. Your role this year is to contribute at a high level and elevate those around you through what you share.\n\nThe 33 year can feel weighty — the sense of responsibility is real. But leading with love and genuine care for others rather than personal recognition keeps the energy clean. This is a year where your presence matters, and your choices ripple outward significantly.\n\n## Focus On\n- Teaching, mentoring, and service\n- Purpose-driven work that impacts others\n- Leading with compassion and integrity\n\n## Avoid\n- Seeking recognition over genuine contribution\n- Taking on more responsibility than you can sustain\n- Ignoring your own needs in service of others`\n    }\n};\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# sourceMappingURL=data:application/json;charset=utf-8;base64,\n//# sourceURL=webpack-internal:///(ssr)/./lib/content.ts\n");

